   multivariate classification showing that the posterior superior temporal
   sulcus (pSTS), previously known to encode polymodal visual and auditory
   representations, encodes information about person identity with
   invariance within and across modality. In particular, pSTS shows
   selectivity for faces, selectivity for voices, classification of face
   identity across image transformations within the visual modality, and
   classification of person identity across modality. (C) 2017 Elsevier
